Code Reference¶

Utils¶

This utility script is for loading the configuration set out in the YAML file located in “config/config.yaml”

utils.config_loader.load_config(path: str = 'config/config.yaml') → Dict¶

Loads YAML configuration as a dictionary

utils.config_loader.verify_files(config: Dict) → List¶

Verifies that the required model file exists. Will return a list of missing file names.

Model Components¶

Module to set up projection heads for both classification and summarization models. Moved from train_model script.

Only final projection wrapper versions are kept here.

class model.model_projection.Seq2SeqWProjection(*args: Any, **kwargs: Any)¶

Class to add a small projection head to summarization model during training.

class model.model_projection.SeqClassWProjection(*args: Any, **kwargs: Any)¶

Modified wrapper for classification model that omits dot product similarity calculations with model outputs. Created to confirm if the code description embeddings are creating a bottleneck. Maintains projection head setup (either individual or MoE)

Module to create Mixture-of-Experts architecture for LLM training.

Prior version of this mudule created experts that were homogeneous in depth and activation type.

class model.mixture_of_experts.MixedMoEProjectionLayer(*args: Any, **kwargs: Any)¶

Mixture-of-Experts projection layer that allows for modification of number of experts and number of selected experts. Designed to be fitted into projection layer of the model.

## This version of the projection is intended to diversify experts (modules) in depth and activation types

num_experts¶

number of experts to create (default 4)

Type:

int

top_k¶

number of top experts to select (default 2)

Type:

int

experts¶

list of projection modules that comprise the MoE architecture

Type:

ModuleList

gate¶

gating network for selecting which experts are active

Type:

nn.Linear

forward(x: torch.Tensor) → torch.Tensor¶

Modified forward pass that uses gate network to select k experts. Set up to use same MLP config as is in classification wrapper.

Parameters:

x (Tensor) – Input tensor to the forward pass [batch, hidden_dim]

Returns:

Output based on MoE [batch, hidden_dim]

Return type:

Tensor
